cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the problem of the reality gap in robotics and proposes a method to narrow it through simulator tuning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the transfer of learned behaviors between simulated and real-world environments, which is a common topic in AI research. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the optimization of physics engine parameters to improve the transfer of simulated solutions, which is a machine learning task. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve visual perception in the simulated and real-world environments. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the interaction between a robotic system and its environment, which is a topic in systems and control.
